The paper discusses reinforcement learning algorithms and their convergence, safety guarantees, and stability, which are all topics related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the integration of reinforcement learning into stochastic optimization, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of operator splitting methods, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the use of Legendre transforms, which is a topic in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
